---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout locale="en" title="Air TM">
  <section class="project-hero"><div class="hero-bg" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0d1b2a,#1b263b,#415a77)"></div><div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="container"><div class="hero-content"><a href="/#results" class="back-link"><svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M15 5L5 10L15 15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>Back</a><h1 class="project-title">Air TM</h1><p class="project-tagline">UX for digital financial platform</p><p class="project-context">Finance / LATAM</p></div></div>
  </section>
  <section class="project-section"><div class="container"><span class="section-label-text"><i>01</i> Problem</span><p class="project-body">Improvement proposal for Airtm, a platform for sending and receiving money across currencies. The interface had visual inconsistencies, complex navigation, and lacked hierarchy for key financial functions.</p></div></section>
  <section class="project-section-alt"><div class="container"><span class="section-label-text"><i>02</i> System</span><p class="project-body">UX proposal with unified design system, side menu, and improved accessibility patterns. Based on user research and acceptance testing.</p></div></section>
  <section class="project-result"><div class="container"><div class="result-box"><h2>Result</h2><p>The proposal delivered a consistent visual foundation and clearer navigation flow, laying groundwork for future product iterations.</p></div></div></section>
</BaseLayout>